[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Overarching concerns about the proposals[bold]2.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]First, t
[normal]here is a genuine risk that all four proposals will lead to the erosion of access to justice, particularly in relation to cases against public bodies.  As a consequence, public bodies may increasingly be able to act with i
[normal]mpunity as the ability of citizens to challenge them is reduced.
[normal]2.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Second, t
[normal]he proposals, which risk depriving the poorest and most vulnerable citizens of a legal remedy, are potentially detrimental to the concept of equality before the law and the ability o
[normal]f all citizens to have equal access to justice.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Legitimacy of  the government's objectives[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To further reduce the cost of legal aid; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To restore 
[normal]public confidence in legal aid.
